---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';

const breadcrumbItems = [
  { href: '/', label: 'Home' },
  { href: '/what-we-do', label: 'What We Do' },
  { href: '/what-we-do/projects', label: 'Projects' },
  { href: '', label: 'Walking For Change' },
];
---

<BaseLayout title='Walking for Change'>
  <Breadcrumb items={breadcrumbItems} />

  <section class='py-13'>
    <div class='max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8'>
      <div class='grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8'>
        <!-- Main blog content -->
        <main class='md:col-span-7 lg:col-span-8'>
          <h1 class='text-4xl hist font-bold mb-4'>Walking for Change:</h1>
          <p class='text-2xl font-semibold mb-6'>A Journey Against Femicide.</p>

          <p class='mb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed'>
            In the heart of Homa Bay town, a quiet revolution began to
            stir—fueled by a shared determination to end the brutal and
            senseless violence against women and girls in our community. As dawn
            broke on a crisp Saturday morning, the streets came alive with the
            steady rhythm of footsteps, each one echoing a powerful message of
            hope, unity, and defiance.
          </p>

          <p class='mb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed'>
            Among the crowd, one figure stood out—you. You chose to walk
            alongside local organizations and fellow advocates, united in
            purpose and unwavering in your resolve. This wasn’t just a walk; it
            was a declaration. A bold affirmation that enough is enough. It was
            a stand against injustice and a step toward a safer, more equitable
            world.
          </p>

          <div class='my-6'>
            <img
              src='/gallery/2.jpg'
              alt='Partnership success'
              class='rounded w-full object-cover'
            />
          </div>

          <p class='mb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed'>
            As you moved through the streets, banners raised high and voices
            joined in unison, a wave of emotion surged through you—anger for the
            lives stolen, sorrow for those who suffered in silence, but above
            all, hope. Hope that through action, awareness, and solidarity, real
            change is not only possible but inevitable.
          </p>
          <p class='mb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed'>
            By midday, the march arrived at the town square, where a stage
            welcomed speeches, songs, and stories. Here, in the heart of the
            community, you stood among leaders, allies, and survivors to share a
            vision: a world where every woman and girl lives free from fear. A
            world shaped not by violence, but by dignity, equity, and respect.
            But your commitment didn’t end when the march was over.
          </p>
          <p class='mb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed'>
            In the days and weeks that followed, you continued to raise your
            voice—lobbying for policy reform, educating others, and providing
            critical support to those affected. Your passion sparked a movement.
            Others joined the cause, inspired by your example and galvanized by
            your determination.
          </p>
          <p class='mb-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed'>
            And so, the movement grew. From whispered conversations to national
            discussions, from small gatherings to public rallies, momentum
            built—transforming personal resolve into a collective force for
            justice. Today, as we reflect on this journey, we see you for who
            you are: a catalyst, a changemaker, a beacon of hope. Your courage
            and compassion remind us all that even in the darkest of times,
            progress is possible when we walk together.
          </p>

          <p class='mb-4 font-semibold text-gray-800'>
            The road ahead may still be long. But with each step we
            take—together—we move closer to a world where femicide is no longer
            a headline, but a tragedy of the past.
          </p>
        </main>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <aside class='md:col-span-5 lg:col-span-4 space-y-6 mt-8 md:mt-0'>
          <div class='bg-gray-100 rounded overflow-hidden shadow'>
            <img
              src='/gallery/4.jpg'
              alt='Partnership success'
              class='w-full object-cover'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='bg-gray-100 rounded overflow-hidden shadow'>
            <img
              src='/gallery/6.jpg'
              alt='Partnership success'
              class='w-full object-cover'
            />
          </div>
          <div class='bg-gray-100 rounded overflow-hidden shadow'>
            <img
              src='/gallery/5.jpg'
              alt='Partnership success'
              class='w-full object-cover'
            />
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
